  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing life-saving COVID-19 protection gear to vulnerable urban communities in Lebanese cities, including refugees and migrants.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving water, sanitation and hygiene assistance in Lebanon (Sabra and Daouk-Ghawash neighbourhoods in Beirut). This UN Habitat project provides personal protective family kits containing basic hygiene necessities and raises awareness about the risks of COVID-19. The project provides life-saving assistance to 3,000 people, including 1,000 women and 1,500 children.</narrative>
  </description>
